verbs.description: nonconcur (third-person singular simple present nonconcurs, present participle nonconcurring, simple past and past participle nonconcurred)

entries.meaning: To dissent or refuse to concur.
examples: MESSAGE FROM THE HOUSE Announcing, the House nonconcurs in Senate amendments to HB 2464 and requests a conference and has appointed Representatives Matlack, Baker and Duncan as conferees on the part of the House.
